1 31<lb/>
2.<lb/>
On the methods that may be adopted<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">for preventing the accidents arising from</hi>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">explosions of the fire damp in coal</hi>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">mines. . by Sir. H D.</hi>
            <lb/>
The accidents arising from the explosion<lb/>
of the fire damp or inflammable gas of<lb/>
coal mines mixed with <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag241"
                ref="#chemical_149"
                type="chemical">
               <term xml:id="tag241">
          atmospherical air
          
        </term>
            </rs>
            <lb/>
are actually becoming more frequent<lb/>
&amp; more terrible in the collieries in the<lb/>
North of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag242"
                ref="#place_121"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag242" type="place">
          England
        </name>
            </rs>.-<lb/>
A committee has been for some time<lb/>
formed at Sunderland for the <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">benevolent</add> purpose of<lb/>
investigating the causes of these accidents<lb/>
&amp; of searching for means of preventing<lb/>
them. the consequence of an invitation<lb/>
from the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag243"
                ref="#person_822"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag243" type="person">
          Rev<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gray
        </name>
            </rs> are of the<lb/>
most active members of this committee<lb/>
