            <lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">12</del> 20 90<lb/>
in the bottom which may be opened or closed according as a<lb/>
a larger or smaller wick is burned in it - An oil lamp<lb/>
I think will be preferred to a candle because it will always<lb/>
stand in the lantern at the same height and the flame<lb/>
will be more regular and this lamp may be introduced<lb/>
from the top of the lantern <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">and trimmed in the same</del>
            <lb/>
