            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">will show the necessity of ventilating that part of the mine In this</del>
            <lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">case the only inconvenience is the extinction of the light. With a</del>
            <lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">common light the loss of life is almost inevitable</del>
            <lb/>
Amongst various plans for preventing accidents from the fire damp<lb/>
it has been proposed <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Some persons have</del> proposed to burn the fire damp in the<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Some persons have</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">
               <unclear>Xx xxxx</unclear> various plans for preventing accidents from the fire damp</add> proposed to burn the fire damp in the<lb/>
mine but this will only render the ventilation more difficult for<lb/>
there will be less respirable air in the residuum of the combustion<lb/>
than in the mixed gas and the ventilation must be greater to<lb/>
free the mine from the choke damp so generated than from<lb/>
the original fire damp<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="126"
