               <lb/>
               <pb n="158" xml:id="pb-158" facs="#i158"/>
               <lb/>
4 130<lb/>
was passed rapidly through <del rend="strikethrough">the cylinder</del>
               <add>it</add>
               <lb/>
               <del rend="strikethrough">so as to</del>
               <add>by pressure</add> from a <del rend="strikethrough">large</del> gazometer &amp; a<lb/>
               <add>pair of double bellows</add> so as to make it a species<lb/>
of <del rend="strikethrough">wind furnace</del> blast furnace<lb/>
yet no explosion took place. -<lb/>
I mentioned in my last communication<lb/>
to the Society that a flame confined<lb/>
in a cylinder of very fine wire gauze<lb/>
did not <del rend="strikethrough">communicate</del> explode<lb/>
a mixture of <rs xml:id="ttag566" ref="#chemical_022" type="chemical">
                  <term xml:id="tag566">
          Oxygene
          
