10 136<lb/>
from which it is disengaged. -<lb/>
Taking all these circumstances into<lb/>
account there appears no<lb/>
difficulty in explaining<lb/>
the facts of the combustion<lb/>
of explosive mixtures within<lb/>
&amp; not without the cylinders: for<lb/>
a current is established from<lb/>
below upwards &amp; the hottest<lb/>
part of the cylinder is where<lb/>
the results of combustion the<lb/>
water <rs xml:id="ttag575" ref="#chemical_058" type="chemical">
                  <term xml:id="tag575">
          Carbonic Acid
          
        </term>
               </rs> or <rs xml:id="ttag576" ref="#chemical_017" type="chemical">
