1<lb/>
177<lb/>
6<lb/>
A <hi rend="underline">few <add>additional practical</add> Onservations on the <add>wire gauze</add> safety</hi>
                     <lb/>
                     <hi rend="underline">lamps for miners</hi> with some evidence<lb/>
of their use.<lb/>
I have already published an account<lb/>
of the researches which led me<lb/>
to discover that explosions <add>&amp; flame</add> are incapable<lb/>
of passing through <add>metallic</add> tissues which are <lb/>
nevertheless very permeable to both<lb/>
light &amp; air &amp; I have described several<lb/>
